  "source": "Lemma: \"Lemma 3.23\"\ngiven: m, n, q is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\nthen:\n. if: m \\:less.than?:/ n\n  then: \\set.theoretic.successor{m} \\:less.than.or.equal:/ n\n. m \\:less.than.or.equal?:/ \\sum:of{m}:and{n}\n. if:\n  . \\set.theoretic.zero \\:less.than?:/ q\n  . \\set.theoretic.zero \\:less.than?:/ n\n  then: \\set.theoretic.zero \\:less.than?:/ \\product:of{q}:and{n}\nDocumented:\n. description: \"Let $m, n, q \\in \\omega$. Then (a) if $m < n$ then $m^+ \\leq n$; (b) $m \\leq m + n$; and (c) if $q > 0$ and $n > 0$ then $qn > 0$.\"\nId: \"c6f806a0-a146-41c3-b0ef-a577c2eba28f\"",
